                <article>
                    <header><h1>How Recent Google Changes Will Affect Private Clubs</h1></header>

                    <p>If you <strong>rely on your club website</strong> to attract new members, promote events, banquets and catering services, then you should read this.</p>

                    <h2>Mobile Searches Now Exceed Computer Searches</h2>
                    <p>Google recently announced the following (full article <a href="http://adwords.blogspot.com/2015/05/building-for-next-moment.html" target="_blank">here</a>):</p>
                    <blockquote>"Billions of times per day, consumers turn to Google for I want-to-know, I want-to-go, I want-to-do, and I want-to-buy moments. And at these times, consumers are increasingly picking 
                        up their smartphones for answers. In fact, <strong>more Google searches take place on mobile devices than on computers</strong> in 10 countries including the US and Japan.  This presents a tremendous 
                        opportunity for marketers to reach people throughout all the new touchpoints of a consumer's path to purchase."</blockquote>

                    <h2>New Google Algorithm Now Rewards Mobile-Friendly Sites</h2>
                    <p>As of April 21, 2015, Google has made a massive change to the way it ranks websites. &nbsp;The change comes down to one very important criterion: <strong>whether your website is 
                            fully optimized for mobile</strong>.</p>
                    <p>Google announced the change on its Webmaster Central Blog back in February and has done a thorough job ever since explaining to marketers and website owners how the change will 
                        affect their site and search traffic. They explained:</p>
                    <blockquote>"Starting April 21, we will be expanding our use of mobile-friendliness as a ranking signal. This change will affect mobile searches in all languages worldwide and will have a significant 
                        impact in our search results. Consequently, users will find it easier to get relevant, high quality search results that are optimized for their devices."</blockquote>

                    <h2>What does this mean to you?</h2>
                    <p>If your club website is not current and not mobile-friendly, there is a very good chance that <strong>your site will not appear near the top of the list</strong> when someone performs a Google search
                        for something associated with your club. &nbsp;This could be potential new members searching for private clubs in the area, or people searching for wedding and banquet services, or Monday outings.  
                        &nbsp;Google is still the #1 search engine and how they rank websites is very important when it comes to landing on the coveted first page of results.</p>
                    <p>Google's <strong>preferred method of website design is called "Responsive Web Design" (RWD)</strong>. &nbsp;With RWD a website will automatically format the pages to <strong>fit on any device</strong>, from desktops to tablets to smart phones.
                        Sites that properly implement RWD will typically rank higher than sites that are not as mobile-friendly..</p>
                    <p>ForeTees implemented RWD throughout our entire product line more than a year ago. &nbsp;We are still the <strong>only provider to offer RWD on the public website pages AND the entire member-only area (website and reservations)!</strong></p>
                    <p>If you are considering an <strong>upgrade to your current website, or you want to properly mobilize your entire online presence</strong>, then please contact us to see 
                        how our RWD solutions can out-perform anything else on the market.</p>
                </article>


